  "texts": [
    "GWAS data was obtained from the Phase 3 summary statistics in Jansen et al.",
    "115, for a total of 30 significant genes.",
    "10 expert-led genes, including APP, MAPT, FOXO3, PSEN1, IGF1, ACT1, SIRT1, PAX6, PSEN2, and APOE, were chosen based on the expert knowledge of our neuroscience co-authors, who recently discovered ADNP and SHANK3 mutations as the key somatic mutation markers of autism linked to AD 116.",
    "In addition, her team has proven that critical somatic mutations in ADNP correlate with AD Tau pathology 99, and verified them as driving an early AD-like Tau pathology in a genomeedited (CRISPR/Cas9) mouse model 117.",
    "In total, 310 genes were selected."
  ],
